data.col_2: Your local agent to this contract may use its own vehicles or can subcontract to another trucking company, however, your local agent is only allowed to subcontract one-tier down. To be clear this means that the subcontracted trucker cannot themselves subcontract out. All subcontractors should be clearly listed and a Due Diligence carried out to ensure they are capable of meeting ASUS requirements while you submit RFQ to ASUS. ASUS must be informed in case of any new subcontractor used during RFQ contract period.

A written contract(security requirements and operation procedure must in place) with trucking company which are complied with ASUS Group requirement, and give top priority to consider the trucking company who has TAPA TSR certification.

The trailer must be equipped with GPS tracking technology. The GPS system should be actively monitored during the transit. In addition, protocols must be in place should an alarm be activated, which alerts a dedicated security company (and/or police) who can attempt to recover the shipment.

The BOX trailer has to be used in any circumstance unless same-day delivery without overnight stay. For same-day delivery without overnight stay, Box trailer is preferred, however, the absolute minimum requirement is anti-slash curtain trailer.

For truck with cargo values more than EUR 500,000, 
- truck and trailer needs to have GPS system and GPS needs to be monitored 24 hours.
- Any deviation GPS tracking shows then action to be taken
- Panic button connected to monitoring center

data.col_1: 3. Pick -Up Procedure in Place (All pick-up procedure are included)

data.col_2:
The procedure must to include at least :
1. Pre-Alert of Truck company/Driver's IDs/Vehicle license plate/Expected arrival time   
2. Cross -Check to avoid any possible fraudulent pick-up
3. Varifiy Driver IDs and record information
Driver has to be reachable by mobile phone during transportation.
The driver has to check if the trailer or container's  seal or lock is damage after every stop or rest period.

During transportation or in the case that driver needs to be temporarily away from truck in any cirsumstance, the container/trailer must be sealed and locked with a locking mechanism which prevents either left or right door of trailer being opened. Samples of locks are shown in appendix.
If it is necessary to refuel then it should be planned at a filling station with adequate security, CCTV and driver should never leave keys inside vehicle.

It is not allowed to leave the truck unless official secured packing lot is used, which has:
    - CCTV
    - Guard
    - Dedicated security barrier
    - Perimeter fencing
    - Sufficient lighting

In the event of delay as a consequence of mechanical problems, breakdown of the vehicle, accidents, traffic jams, road diversions and the like, the driver is obliged to inform the operations center and not to leave the vehicle. If the driver is injured and sent to hospital, your representative must be there to secure ASUS cargos until the following steps are well arranged under good security management.

When picking-up container from a terminal, please carefully check if seal is missing or broken. In case of any seal abnormality (missing or broken), please take pictures, inform ASUS immeidately of seal status with photos, and also add another security lock to protect a container. The following steps will be adivsed by ASUS.

For local delivery, parking outside a secure parking lot (as defined) is not allowed. Where a slot time is missed or shipment is rejected, ASUS must be informed immediatley. These cargos have to be closely monitored and return to the secured DC without overnight stay outside.

data.Unnamed: 2: There must be a written contract in place with the DC clearly specifying security and opeational requirements
Fence should be protected so as to prevent thieves easily climbing over into the yard.e.g. electrified or barbed wire atop
The appointed security company should have response time to site of less than 10 min.
the secutity company has roaming security car / tag system.
Any Security guard should be equipped with a mobile panic button which he can press to alert security party.
Where possible a 24/7 security guard should be on site.

Alarm system should have dual code capability i.e. if the person opening th facility is doing so under duress they can enter a different number which will open the facility but also send a silent alarm to security company.
A written Hot work Permit is required for any hot works to be carried out, with a minimum 1 hour fire watch.
Battery charging area should be in clear and well-ventilated area with sufficient airflow and be removed 5m from any combustible materials.
Fire-suppression equipment (fire extinguishers, Fire Hoses, Sprinklers) should be clear of any obstructions.

CCTV need to cover all of :
- the entry /exit points 
- racking lanes (Isles) 
- inside (covering entrances)
   including the dock, so loading and unloading could be clearly viewed  
- outside (covering the perimeter)
CCTV is supported by strong lighting which is on during night hours.
DC must keep CCTV record at least 30days
Location should have smoke detectors and alarm in place to quickly detect fire. Alarm must automatically alert the appropriate person (guard, security company, fire department)
Motion Detectors / Motion beams are needed throughout the facility, including all possible entry points & dock doors
All Motion Detectors / Motion beams should be anti-mask and linked to alarm system & security company who monitor 24/7 and have protocols in place to react should any abnormalities occur.
